03/05/2010
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Dragan Kujovic, a parliament member with the ruling Democratic Party of Socialists, passed away on Saturday (May 1st) at the age of 62 after a lengthy illness.
He was a fervent supporter of Montenegro's independence and had held a series of posts throughout his political career, from lawmaker and deputy parliament speaker to education minister.
He was buried on Sunday.
(Radio Free Europe, Srna - 02/05/10;
Cafemontenegro - 01/05/10)
